  "doc_id": "33966",
  "text": "Oxiconazole active substance was selected from this group because it has low-medium molecular weight, high permeability, no deep irritation, high local bioavailability and good compatibility with polymers. Transdermally administered thermosensitive gels are new drug delivery systems that have been studied frequently since they have in situ activity depending on the temperature [CITATION_1] . The thermosensitive gels are superior to the conventional gels in terms of stability, ease of use for patients, improved local bioavailability, and efficacy at low doses, easy preparation and low production costs.",
